quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  10,93,"And We established the Children of Israel in a secure abode, and We provided them with good things; and they disagreed not until knowledge had come unto them. Verily, your Lord will judge between them on the Day of Resurrection concerning that whereon the"
  10,94,"And if you are in doubt of that which We have revealed unto you, ask those who read the Book before you; verily, the truth has come to you from your Lord. So be not you of those who doubt"
  10,95,"And be not of those who reject the Signs of Allah, for then you will be of the losers"
  10,96,"Verily, those against whom the word of your Lord has been pronounced will not believe"
  10,97,"Even though there come to them every sign, until they see the grievous doom"
  10,98,"If only there were a community that had believed and profited from its faith. But none did except the people of Jonah. When they believed We removed from them the Torment of Disgrace in this world, and We gave them provision for a while"
  10,99,"But had your Lord willed, all who are in the earth would have believed together. Would you force men to become believers"
  10,100,It is not for any soul to believe save by the permission of Allah; He sets uncleanness on those who have no sense
  10,101,"Say, \"Behold what is in the heavens and in the earth! But Signs and Warners avail not a people who do not believe"
  10,102,"What expect they but the like of the days of those who passed away before them? Say, \"Wait you then! Verily, I, too, will wait with you"
  10,103,"Then will We save Our Messengers and those who believe, as is fitting to Us, in like manner as before"